FBIS3-52762 "drnes005_w_94001" FBIS-NES-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 Sri Lanka LTTE To Execute Mahattaya for Betrayal BK0701121494 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service in English 1045 GMT 7 Jan 94 BK0701121494 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The LTTE [Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam] has confirmed that its former deputy leader Gopalaswamy Mahendraraja, alias Mahattaya, has been sentenced to death. According to early intelligence reports, his execution has been tentatively fixed for the 16th of this month. A news dispatch received by LANKAPUVATH from London states that this week's edition of the official LTTE news bulletin (KHALLATATHIL) published in London announced that Mahattaya has been sentenced to death. He is also a former leader of the political wing of the terrorist group. Mahattaya is reported to be held in an LTTE prison in Jaffna. The main accusation against him is that he has served as an agent of India's Research and Analysis Wing and allegedly provided vital information which led to the Indian Navy apprehending the MV Ahatta on board [as heard] which LTTE's international representative and former deputy leader Sadasivam Krishnakumar, alias Kittu, was transporting a shipload of highly sophisticated weapons for use by the LTTE.
